-- Uganda Owes Oil Companies $492.5 Million, New Vision Reports
-- B y   F r e d   O j a m b o
-- 2012-04-04T07:34:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-04/uganda-owes-oil-companies-492-5-million-new-vision-reports.html
Uganda  owed oil companies $492.5
million in recoverable exploration spending by the end of the
2010-11 year, New Vision said, citing an auditor-general report.  The money was invested by the oil explorers and will be
recovered from government once production of the resource
starts, the Kampala-based newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fred Ojambo in Kampala at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  